    "stat_block": {
        "type": "stat_block",
        "subtype": "equipment",
        "text": "This garment appears to be an ordinary robe until donned, at which point numerous strange and alien eyes of varied shapes and colors open and blink across its fabric. While wearing the robe, you gain a +3 item bonus to Perception checks, and you constantly benefit from the effects of a 2nd-level *see invisibility* spell.  \n  \n You can also see powerful magic auras. The highest-level magic aura within 30 feet of you glows in a color that reveals its school to you and allows you to determine where the effect originates. This can narrow down the origin point of the effect to a 5-foot-cube, but not more precisely than that.  \n  \n The *robe of eyes* is not without its dangers. If any spell with the light trait is cast on you or your square while you are wearing the robe, you are blinded for a number of rounds equal to the spell\u2019s level unless you succeed at a Fortitude save against the spell\u2019s DC.",
        "level": 17,
        "image": {
            "type": "image",
            "name": "Robe of Eyes",
            "image": "Robe_of_Eyes.webp"
        },
